\pard\f0\fs28    Very variable. Robust plants with thick, fleshy, unlobed or only slightly lobed leaves have been called{\b  S. crassifolius} Willd., {\i Sp. Pl.} {\b 3}: 1982 (1803), and contrast very strongly with small spring-flowering ephemerals with only slightly fleshy leaves. Nevertheless, a series of intermediates seems to connect all the variants.
