\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 61. S. petraeus} Boiss. & Reuter, {\i Pugillus} 59 (1852). Subglabrous, erect annual up to 50 cm with ascending branches mainly in the upper half. Basal leaves ovate, entire or dentate, shortly petiolate; cauline ovate-lanceolate, obtuse, dentate to shallowly lobed, auriculate-amplexicaul. Capitula few, 20-30 mm in diameter. Involucre c. 10 mm; supplementary bracts absent. Ligules c. 13, 8-10 mm, yellow. Achenes c. 3 mm, hairy.{\i  Limestone rocks. • S.W. Spain.} Hs.
